FBIS4-33559 "drlat110_c_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-110 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 MEXICO PGR Arrests 13 for Gun Running; Weapons Seized PGR Arrests 13 for Gun Running; Weapons Seized PA0606153794 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 6 Jun 94 PA0606153794 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 6 Jun 94 Spanish BFN [From the "Early Morning" newscast] [Text] The Attorney General's Office [PGR] reported that 13 gun runners were arrested in several operations. At the same time, 10,159 ammunition rounds of diverse caliber, 550 grams of dynamite, and 17 weapons were seized. The PGR reported that the operations are continuing in order to determine the origin and final destination of the weapons as well as possible participation of other individuals in the gun running activity. The PGR indicated that the largest weapons' seizure took place at the Sonora checkpoint, where 7,600 ammunition rounds of various calibers and seven weapons were confiscated.
